### [Proverbs Chapter 10](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 10:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 10:2</span></span>

Of wickedness - Such as are got by any sort of wicked practices. Death -
Often from temporal, and always from eternal death.

[Proverbs 10:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 10:5</span></span>

Gathereth - The fruits of his field. In summer - In harvest. He that
improved the opportunities of doing good to himself and others.

[Proverbs 10:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 10:6</span></span>

Violence - Their own violence or injustice. This may be an allusion to
the ancient custom of covering the mouths and faces of condemned
malefactors.

[Proverbs 10:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 10:8</span></span>

Who receive - Is ready to hear and obey the precepts of God and men.
Fall - Into mischief.

[Proverbs 10:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 10:9</span></span>

Surely - Or, securely, or confidently, as the word properly signifies;
quietly resting upon God's favour and gracious providence for his
protections. Known - His wickedness shall be publickly discovered.

[Proverbs 10:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 10:10</span></span>

Winketh - That secretly designs mischief against others, as this phrase
is used, [Psa 35:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa035.htm#019.md).

[Proverbs 10:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">pro 10:13</span></span>

Wisdom - This wisdom shews itself in his speech. A rod - Rebukes from
God and men.

[Proverbs 10:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 10:14</span></span>

Lay up - In their minds, to be brought forth upon fit occasions.
Knowledge - Whereby they may be enabled to speak both what, and when it
is seasonable. But - Fools are more forward to lay out than to lay up,
and for want of knowledge speak much and foolishly, whereby they
frequently bring destruction upon themselves.

[Proverbs 10:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 10:15</span></span>

Wealth - It often redeems him from dangers and calamities. Poverty - Is
the cause of their ruin.

[Proverbs 10:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 10:16</span></span>

The labour - The fruit of his labour, to the preservation of this life,
and obtaining eternal life. Fruit - The fruit of all their labour tends
to sin, and serves only for fuel to mens pride and luxury.

[Proverbs 10:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 10:18</span></span>

Lying lips - With flattering words. He here condemns two opposite vices,
secret hatred, and manifest slander.

[Proverbs 10:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 10:20</span></span>

Is - Of great worth and use. Heart - And consequently the tongue.

[Proverbs 10:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 10:21</span></span>

Feed - By their wise discourses and counsels. Die - They have not wisdom
to preserve themselves, much less to feed others.

[Proverbs 10:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 10:26</span></span>

So - Unserviceable and vexatious.

[Proverbs 10:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 10:28</span></span>

Gladness - Shall be accomplished, and turned into enjoyment.

[Proverbs 10:29](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">pro 10:29</span></span>

The way - The way of God's precepts. Strength - Gives strength, support,
and protection.

[Proverbs 10:30](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">pro 10:30</span></span>

Never be removed - They shall live happily here, and eternally in
heaven. The earth - They shall not have so much as a quiet abode upon
earth; much less shall they have any possession in heaven.

[Proverbs 10:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro010.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 10:32</span></span>

The lips - Knowledge is here ascribed to the lips, as it is to the
hands, [Psa 78:72](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#072.md), because they are
conducted by knowledge and wisdom. Acceptable - What is truly worthy of
acceptation.

